ts in both, do field-level merge\n3. Field-level merge (recursive):\n   - For each field in union of base/ours/theirs keys:\n     - If only ours changed: take ours\n     - If only theirs changed: take theirs\n     - If both changed to same value: take either (no conflict)\n     - If both changed to different values: conflict (use ours for merged output)\n     - If field is object on all sides: recurse\n4. Return MergeResult with merged content, conflicts, and applied flag\n\n### Deep Cloning\n\nUse `structuredClone()` for all storage and retrieval boundaries.\n\n### Version IDs\n\nMonotonic counter: `v1`, `v2`, `v3`, etc. Global across all branches.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
