+# Versioned Document Store Design
+
+## Architecture
+
+### Module Structure
+- `src/types.ts` - All interfaces and types (Version, MergeResult, Conflict, internal types)
+- `src/merge.ts` - Three-way structural merge algorithm
+- `src/document-store.ts` - DocumentStore class implementation
+- `src/index.ts` - Re-exports
+
+### Internal Data Model
+
+```
+DocumentStore:
+  branches: Map<branchName, BranchState>
+  currentBranch: string (default "main")
+  versionCounter: number (monotonic)
+  forkPoints: Map<childBranch, Map<parentBranch, BranchSnapshot>>
+
+BranchState:
+  documents: Map<docId, DocumentRecord>
+
+DocumentRecord:
+  versions: Version[] (chronological)
+  content: object | null (null = deleted)
+  deleted: boolean
+```
+
+### Branch Fork Point Tracking
+
+When `createBranch(name, fromBranch?)` is called:
+1. Deep clone the source branch's documents as a snapshot
+2. Store in `forkPoints[newBranch][sourceBranch]` = snapshot
+3. Also copy the full BranchState to the new branch
+
+This snapshot serves as the "common ancestor" (base) for three-way merge.
+
+### Three-Way Merge Algorithm
+
+`merge(sourceBranch)` into current branch:
+
+1. Look up fork point between source and current branch
+2. For each document across base, ours (current), theirs (source):
+   - If doc only exists in one side (created after fork), take it
+   - If doc deleted on one side but modified on other, conflict
+   - If doc deleted on one side and unchanged on other, accept deletion
+   - If doc exists in both, do field-level merge
+3. Field-level merge (recursive):
+   - For each field in union of base/ours/theirs keys:
+     - If only ours changed: take ours
+     - If only theirs changed: take theirs
+     - If both changed to same value: take either (no conflict)
+     - If both changed to different values: conflict (use ours for merged output)
+     - If field is object on all sides: recurse
+4. Return MergeResult with merged content, conflicts, and applied flag
+
+### Deep Cloning
+
+Use `structuredClone()` for all storage and retrieval boundaries.
+
+### Version IDs
+
+Monotonic counter: `v1`, `v2`, `v3`, etc. Global across all branches.
